  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>The problem is that mysite/account/views.py does post['password1'].

If a user doesn't submit a password, that's a KeyError waiting to happen!

The right way to fix this is to write a test that tests the following:

* Submit a POST to mysite.account.views.signup_do that has no password1 key in 
the POST
* Make sure a the form doesn't call that valid
* Make sure no user is created
* Implicitly make sure there is no Error 500

(Right now, this test would hit the KeyError.)</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
